b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both DeepL and memoQ share a solid foundation of core features including Machine Translation, Glossary, Api Access, File Formats. Where DeepL pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Real Time, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. On the other hand, memoQ uniquely offers Translation Memory and Quality Assurance and Custom Models, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, DeepL holds an overall score of 9/10 and an ease of use score of 10/10, while memoQ scores 8/10 overall and 5/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, DeepL offers a more budget-friendly entry point at Free, compared to memoQ's starting price of $770/year. DeepL has a notable advantage here with its free plan, allowing you to get started without any financial commitment. memoQ does not currently offer a free tier, which means you will need to pay from day one."}]]}]
