f:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. DeepL is best suited for businesses, translators, content teams, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. memoQ, meanwhile, shines for professional translators, LSPs, translation agencies, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2017, DeepL describes itself as \"AI-powered translation tool renowned for natural and accurate translations.\" memoQ, established in 2004, positions itself as \"Professional CAT tool and translation management system for linguists.\" With 13 years between them, memoQ brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while DeepL offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
10:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **DeepL** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (9.0 vs 8.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean memoQ is a poor choice — far from it. memoQ excels in its own right, particularly for professional translators and LSPs.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value best translation quality for european languages, go with DeepL. If powerful professional cat tool matters more to you, memoQ is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
